AI Learning & Memory
BrainCore tracks word frequencies; stores learned chunks as JSON.
Prevents duplicate learning using file hashes & source tracking.
Compatible with Windows, macOS, Linux, Raspberry Pi.
Resource Monitoring
Checks RAM & CPU via psutil; fallback if not installed.
Lightweight; works on desktops, servers, or Pi.
Internet Learning
Fetches content from:
Tavily API (topics: AI, robotics, IoT, etc.)
RSS feeds (NYTimes Technology)
Reddit (r/technology top posts)
Wikipedia summaries
Requires network; compatible with desktop, server, Pi.
Direct Learning Utilities
learn_text_content() & learn_text_directly() add words to BrainCore.
Fully local; no network needed.
Query System
query_ai(text) returns top matching words from BrainCore.
Offline, low resource usage.
Raspberry Pi / Remote Device
Queries HTTP endpoint (FLIPPER_ENDPOINT) for remote integration.
Network required; works with Pi or any HTTP device.
Flask Dashboard
Web UI shows BrainCore, RAM/CPU, logs, and query input.
Runs on port 5001; accessible from local network.
Lightweight; Pi-compatible.
Background Loops
Internet learning loop fetches Tavily, RSS, Reddit periodically.
Main loop refreshes BrainCore, queries Pi, and logs stats.
Uses Python threading; minimal resource usage.
Module Installation & Compatibility
Auto-installs psutil, numpy, cv2 (headless), flask, tavily.
Works on Windows, macOS, Linux; headless OpenCV for GUI-less systems.
Device Summary
Local learning & queries: ✅ Desktop, Pi, minimal devices
Network features (Tavily, RSS, Reddit, Pi): ✅ Desktop, Pi; ⚠ Network required
Flask Dashboard: ✅ Desktop, Pi; ⚠ Python + network
OpenCV processing: ✅ Desktop, Pi; ✅ headless
